<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/504> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #504" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 5.31.6, cf. 9.34.20-21; and Dion. Hal. 1.74.6; Fast. Cap. ([- - -Iul]ius Sp. f. Vopisci n. I[- - -]); Plin. NH 33.16; Fest. 500 L; Degrassi 30f., 100, 386f." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/503> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #503" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Beloch (RG 80) doubts this censorship on the basis of Festus (500 L), but Dion. Hal. mentions a census two years before the capture of Rome by the Gauls and Pliny lists the number of citizens of that period." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/463> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #463" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.61.1; Diod. 14.17.1; Fast. Cap. ([- -]) Iulus II; [- -Capit]olin. Barb[at.]; [- -Cinc]innatus II; the others entire, Furius with numeral II); Chr. 354 (Iulo II et Mamertino); Degrassi 28f., 98, 380f. These began the siege of Veii (Liv. 4.61.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/462> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #462" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Diod. gives the number as six, but omits Cincinnatus, Furius, and Aemilius; and has Mamilius for Manlius. On T. Quinctius see 421; he was Capitolini f. (Liv. 4.43.1). For Iulius' cognomen, see 489, note 1 (Tullus, Liv.; Iulus, Fast. Cap.). On Furius, see 413, note 1; the numeral in Livy is tertium. Livy's praenomen for Aemilius, M., is corrected to M'. as in Fast. Cap.; for his cognomen Livy has Mamercus. These magistrates are differently ordered in each of our three chief sources. Livy's order is followed above." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/454> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #454" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 4.56-57; Diod. 13.104.1; Fast. Cap. ([- -] Vopisc[i] n. Iulus; [- -] A. f. M. n. Cossus; [- -] f. Q. n. Ahala); Chr. 354 (Iulo et Cosso); Degrassi 28f., 98, 378f. Servilius named a Dictator against the opposition of his colleagues (Liv. 4.56.8-57.6)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/453> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #453" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Iulius' cognomen is given as Tullius or Tullus in Livy, Iulus in Fast. Cap.; see 489, note 1. The filiation is given in Fast. Cap. on 393, Censors." .
